# Code Quality and Style Rules

## Spring Boot 3 Best Practices
- Use Spring Boot 3.x features including Virtual Threads for high concurrency
- Implement proper Spring Security configuration with JWT and API key authentication
- Use Spring Data JPA with proper entity relationships and validation
- Apply @RestController with proper HTTP status codes and ResponseEntity
- Implement proper exception handling with @ControllerAdvice
- Use @Transactional appropriately for database operations
- Apply Spring Boot configuration properties with @ConfigurationProperties

## GraalVM Native Image Compliance
- Avoid reflection usage; use compile-time configuration when needed
- Use Spring Boot native hints for third-party libraries
- Prefer constructor injection over field injection
- Use @RegisterReflectionForBinding for DTOs and entities
- Avoid dynamic proxy creation patterns
- Use build-time initialization where possible

## Code Structure and Architecture
- Follow clean architecture principles with proper separation of concerns
- Use service layer pattern with interfaces for business logic
- Implement proper DTOs for API request/response objects
- Use MapStruct or similar for object mapping
- Apply proper validation with Bean Validation annotations
- Create custom exceptions for business logic errors
- Use Spring profiles for different environments

## Java and Coding Standards
- Use Java 21+ features including Virtual Threads, pattern matching, and records
- Prefer immutable objects and records for data transfer
- Use Optional for nullable return types
- Apply proper null checks and validation
- Use meaningful variable and method names
- Keep methods small and focused on single responsibility
- Use streams and functional programming where appropriate
- Apply proper logging with SLF4J and structured logging
